ZCZC GE19
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 242300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING A WEAK LOW PRESSURE AREA 1004 LIES OVER FORTIES EXTENDING
ACROSS MUCH OF THE N SEA. AT THE SAME TIME ANOTHER WEAK LOW 1005 LIES JUST
TO THE W OF ICELAND. DURING TUESDAY THE N SEA LOW MOVS SLWY NWARDS TOWARDS
SHETLAND BEFORE MOV NW ACROSS THE FAEROES ON WEDNESDAY. THEREAFTER WKN AND
DISSIPATING AT THE EXPENSE OF THE ICELANDIC LOW THAT MOVS SLWY SWARDS AND
THEN SEWARDS ON TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY TO LIE ACROSS THE N OF THE UK. THIS
LOW THEN MOVS NWARDS TO BE LOCATED NEAR THE NERN ISLES 998 BY THURSDAY.
THROUGHOUT THE PERIOD HIGH PRESSURE IS MAINTAINED ACROSS OR NEAR TO THE
AZORES WITH A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE EXTENDING TOWARDS BISCAY. NO GALES
ARE EXP ACROSS CULLERCOATS DURING THE PERIOD. HOWEVER STRG WINDS MAY DEVELOP
IN HUMBER AND THAMES ON WEDNESDAY NIGHT PERHAPS EXTENDING TO DOGGER FISHER
AND GERMAN BIGHT ON THURSDAY
